A jet of flames burst from Thassalin's jaws as the colossal Thraki set fire to a specific patch of the forest, then circled above, observing it for a while. Oddly, as it had slowed down, the strange sounds of cries behind it had stopped. Thassalin had forgotten that he had passengers on his back.
"Come on, Tenuk, you've already turned into Thraki before!"
"My flight is very different. I don't let myself be violently lifted by an enormous pink dragon!"
"It's not that unpleasant, is it, Kayel?"
Kayel was clearly not in agreement with Nyssi; he seemed less black than usual and had planted his claws into the back of Thassalin, to the point of drawing blood from the Thraki, yet obviously, he didn't care much about it. Still, Thassalin had realized that he had terrified his new friends and had found a clearing to land.
"MY APOLOGIES, I SMELLED A SMOKE. I HAD TO CHECK."
"Toujours obligé de nous traîner ici avec toi?" said Tenuk as he slid down from the back of Thassalin, sliding along his tail. "And we left Retvik behind! We abandoned our great and strong warrior! How will he catch up with us?"
"He'll find a way," Nissy retorted. "Retvik is slow, but not stupid."
"Okay, but does Retvik know how to drive?"
Nissy blinked and turned back to Tenuk. "Of course he knows how to drive."
"Have you ever seen Retvik driving a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like you, and I've never seen him drive anything like Kayel's cute little car either. And if he's started coming to work by car, it's only because YOU drive us there. He just has that bike."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Thassalin suddenly burst into laughter, and no one understood why he was laughing. It took him a bit too long to regain his composure.
"I'M SORRY, BUT I IMAGINED YOUR BIG FRIEND IN ARMOR ON A TINY BIKE INTENDED FOR CHILDREN TEMTHAN. IT WAS SO FUNNY! I WOULD HAVE LOVED TO BE ABLE TO READ MINDS. THAT WAS A PRECIOUS THOUGHT! ONE I CAN'T SHARE!"
Kayel laughed, imagining what Thassalin was thinking. "Yes, that's right. But what did you pick up and why did you fly away so quickly?"
Thassalin grunted, took off, and vanished briefly before returning and dropping a carcass in front of Nyssi. It was an Orothrack, a golden and white dragon-like creature, very rare. But it was missing its head. "ANOTHER DEATH. I HEAR THEIR CRIES. I FEEL THEIR BLOOD. I AM PROGRAMMED TO PROTECT AND HUNT. AS YISINI DEMANDS. THE CREATURES ARE NEAR."
The mighty Thraki froze suddenly. Nyssi and Kayel too, their attention drawn to an opening in the clearing. Something large and black was staring at them, whistling. Whatever it was, it opened two enormous pairs of wings and flew straight at Thassalin, not sparing the three smaller beings in its path. Kayel and Tenuk managed to take cover just in time, but Nyssi was pulled along and almost thrown onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacts to the aggression by grabbing Nissy and throwing her over his back, using his exceptionally long and dexterous tail, before taking off. The black two-winged creature rushed after them quickly.
Kayel exhaled as he drew his rifle from his back, then opened a pouch containing a belt of ammunition. He slung it across his body for easy access, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were no longer visible.
"Hé Tenuk, you up for turning into something that flies?" asked Kayel.
"Will you chase them?" or "Do you want to chase them?"
"Yes, of course!"
But... one of them is a giant monster!
"And so what? I currently have an ultra-powerful rifle in my hands, ready to use. I just need to see him to shoot him."
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to create some space. With a weak, slightly pained growl, his body expanded, his fur was replaced by scales, and his arms transformed into wings. He quickly reverted back to his normal light blue Thraki form, but his eyes remained red.
Climb.
Having regained a more normal appearance, Thraki now had a scaled back covering on his back, but a pair of spines had also grown there, useful for Kayel to grip. Tenuk needed a little time to take off, but once in the air, he quickly oriented himself and attempted to pursue.
However, Tenuk and Kayel quickly realized they were not alone. A second dark creature emerged from below, and Tenuk barely managed to avoid it.
I suppose it's the other big scary monster that was troubling Lanex? Kayel furrowed his brow as he tried to shoot the second creature, missed his target, and quickly reloaded his weapon.
Tenuk did not react. He was too focused on his flight toward Nyssi and Thassalin, despite the other creature chasing them. Kayel clumsily spun around to face the monster. The fact that it was pursuing them was an advantage for Kayel, as it made it easier for him to aim and shoot. Two shots passed through the creature's upper wings, and it howled in pain before disappearing again among the trees. Kayel didn't know if it was still following them, but it would certainly not be able to catch up.
Further away, Nyssi clung desperately, while Thassalin circled around, firing streams of fire at the darkened monster. Although the creature was clearly wounded, it seemed furious and determined to fight on, and the fireballs did not seem to have the desired effect. When Thassalin straightened up, Nyssi seized the opportunity to draw his weapon, a reliable rifle. It was of course not designed for such a situation, but a volley of shots would surely at least deter the black beast, wouldn't it?
